main event: A civilian observed a torpedo-shaped, silvery object traveling at high speed over Condamine, Queensland, Australia on February 7, 1951.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 25 seconds before disappearing,The object was described as being torpedo-shaped and silvery in color,The sighting duration was short but the object appeared to be traveling at a very high rate of speed, There was no physical evidence or photographs associated with the sighting, Another witness reported seeing eight to nine circular objects flying in a triangular formation at a high altitude.
witness description: A civilian who was observing the sky.
